The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 CII paints rosy picture for first half 

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, June 19: A business outlook survey conducted by the Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) for the period April-September 2005 reveals that industry expects higher orders, increased capital investments and improved capacity utilisation during the first half.

 The business confidence index (BCI) for the period stands at 65.7 points, up 0.9 points over the October 2004-March 2005 period.

 The increase in the overall confidence index is in line with the expectation of the 219 companies that responded to the CII business outlook survey. 

 The current situation index (CSI), which compares the current business conditions with the previous six months, stands 0.7 points higher at 63.8 compared with the previous period.

 This indicates that during the previous six months the economy has picked up according to industry expectations, the survey said. 




